			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">An email from MIke Erlandson, chair of the Minnesota DFL (Democrats):
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Dear DFLer,
<br />

<br />
Many of you have shared your concerns over protecting the rights of voters in Ohio and in other parts of our nation.  I want you to know that your concerns have not fallen on deaf ears.  To those of you who volunteered countless hours to get out the vote here in Minnesota  producing a record turnout that hasnt been seen here since 1960  it is critical that you know your work was not in vain and that the Democratic Party at the national level is working to ensure a full and legitimate count of every single vote in this election. 
<br />

<br />
I am writing to you to tell you about two important developments regarding voter protection issues. 
<br />

<br />
First, the Democrats on the House Committee on the Judiciary will hold a hearing on Wednesday morning at 9 a.m. CST to discuss election irregularities in the pivotal state of Ohio during the 2004 presidential Election.  The hearing will be streamed live on the internet at <a href="http://www.pacifica.org" target="_blank">www.pacifica.org</a> and <a href="http://www.kpfa.org" target="_blank">www.kpfa.org</a>, if you wish to tune in. 
<br />

<br />
Second, with regards to the vote count in Ohio, after consulting with the Partys Voting Rights Institute staff, Voting Protection Coordinators, Ohio legal team, Party activists, supporters, elected officials, and others, and after reviewing available information, the Democratic National Committee has decided to conduct a thorough investigation of key election issues arising from the conduct of the 2004 general election in Ohio.
<br />

<br />
This investigative study will address the legitimate questions and concerns that have been raised in Ohio and will develop factual information that will be critically important in crafting further key election reforms. This project seeks to answer such questions as:
<br />

<br />

<br />
Why did so many people have to wait in line in certain Ohio precincts and not others? 
<br />
Why weren't there enough machines in some counties and not others? 
<br />
Why were so many Ohioans forced to cast provisional ballots? 
<br />

<br />
We do not expect either the recount in Ohio or the DNCs investigation to overturn the results of this election, but both are vital to protecting every American's right to vote.
<br />

<br />
The Minnesota DFL hopes to gain useful information through the DNCs investigation, as Minnesota will be required to implement Congress Help America Vote Act  which will require changes in our voting system over the next couple of years.  We will continue to keep a watchful eye on these voter protection issues as they arise in the State Legislature and at the national level, and will work to keep you informed.
<br />

<br />
Thank you for your hard work and continued support.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />

<br />
Mike Erlandson
<br />
Minnesota DFL Party Chair
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
