				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Madrix,
<br />
  I can have only urged that a statistically meaningful recount be completed.  You have only blathered about how NeoCon's should be allowed to win without a statistically accurate count.  Neither of the counts so far in Wa State (backwater as we may be to you - but aren't you from some backwater state, too?) are statistically meaningful.  They both have equalled 'within the margin of error'.  That is it.
<br />

<br />
  Personally, I have had a nice long discussion (1+hour) with my NeoCon Dad recently (over digesting turkey) about this subject and I argued for a tie.  A tie decided by an 1889 silver dollar coin-flip, after all of the recounts were legally done... an 1889 silver dollar that I will gladly provide, completely authenticated by any coin authentication/grading service of anyones choosing (I have several - 1889 is when WA became WA State BTW).
<br />

<br />
  I just think that anyone who argues for 'premature electulation' is only in it for themselves, and not in it to ensure that the process produces a valid winner.  Are you interested in valid election results, or just election results favorable to your candidate?
<br />

<br />
That is the issue.  Are you arguing for the 'winner' or for the 'real winner' (whether or not they are different or the same).  I am arguing for the 'real winner' to be decided by the most statistically meaningful count possible.  I truly don't care who the winner is as much as that the correct processes are followed to ensure that the count is as accurate as possible.  The processes will carry on far beyond this election and be far more important in the end than the winner.  Especially in WA.  I asked my Dad what the Governor of WA State actually did, and we both concluded that statistically it 'wasn't that much'.
<br />

<br />
So talk more about the process and less about who won or lost within the processes that my or may not be broken.  Or return your nose to someone elses #17 butt-cheeks.  Take your pick.
<br />

<br />
Ozbee
