				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The case in Washington supports the stand that the margin for error is not discriminatory as to which party suffers. The recount found 2500 more votes and the results did not change. 
<br />

<br />
Not to say that they cannot which is why there are mandatory recounts depending on the margin of victory. 
<br />

<br />
But without evidence of cheating at the polls and voting irregularities there is no reason for a 3rd or 4th recount to make sure that every vote counts when in reality they just want to try to make sure that the results change. 
<br />

<br />
It goes back to the point that as a politician there is nothing to gain by putting the public through such a challenge. Nixon realized this. Kerry realized it as well.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">End the hypocrisy!</span>
<br />

<br />
