There are already two recounts declaring that Bush won Ohio by a massive margin.  Should a third recount emerge showing that Kerry won Ohio, that recount is instantly and automatically suspect simply because it falls so far out of line with the other observed data.  It's called an "outlier".  And any fool who would automatically assign more weight to the outlier than to the other recounts has no grasp of statistics at all.
