				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To whom it may concern...
<br />

<br />
It ain't about me.  It ain't about you.  It's about recounts, and whether they are worthwhile.  Since I am from WA and not OH, I see and know more about WA.  Here's somethings to chew on.
<br />

<br />
The first recount found over 2500 missing votes, and narrowed the race considerably.  That struck me as odd, that we 'found' so many votes after one machine recount.  I wondered why?  Not why is one candidate or the other winning, but why such a big difference (almost x10 the difference between the 2 candidates votes).
<br />

<br />
Chew on this for those of you that don't want the votes counted carefully.  From the BS (Bremerton Sun - of Kitsap Co. WA):
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The hand recount found 154 more votes than a previous manual recount. Kitsap's 10-year-old optical scan equipment was blamed for the discrepancy.  
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Why?
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Election supervisor Dolores Gilmore said they have to walk a middle ground in setting the sensitivity of the scanners, which count a vote if two sides of an arrow corresponding to a candidate are connected by a line. 
<br />

<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And that from a county that contributed less than %5 of the vote total, but the most significant recount total reported so far.  We are fair and civil about it here, with plenty of both parties observers looking over the recount.  No one here is complaining about the process.
<br />

<br />
It's here at <a href="http://www.kitsapsun.com" target="_blank">www.kitsapsun.com</a> , if you care.  Get off your ass and click the links yourself, they keep changing them.
<br />

<br />
Hmmmmm.....   Machine recounts are faulty and hand recounts are more accurate and make everyone feel better about the process?  Getthefuggouttahere.  154 votes out of slightly more than 110,000 in Kitsap were found in the hand recount for the reasons listed above.  That's an error rate of 0.15% in one of the more technologically advanced counties here.  Even both parties agreed that the recount here in Kitsap was done fairly and accurately.  See, you actually can do a recount with civility and both sides can agree on how it was done.
<br />

<br />
The point is and always has been 'count the votes carefully', and quit bitching about them being careful and about counting carefully.  We NEVER know the counting error rate until we recount.  And the only damage that is caused by recounting is to those that don't want to know how accurate the count is.
<br />

<br />
The estimated TOTAL cost of the recount in WA is borne by the requestor, as the REPUBLICAN Sec. of State here requested from the Demo who paid for the recount, so when the State says send a check for $730,000 (the latest # I heard) they were not expecting Joe taxpayer to bear ANY of the cost beyond what they reasonably expected it to cost.  There should be no hidden cost that I have to bear.  That number was decided by a Repub SoS, and NO ONE in WA State is complaining about that number.  In fact, NO ONE in WA State is complaining about the Repub SoS here.  He is doing a stand-up job of handling a very difficult situation admirably.  He is an honorable man, and I don't expect anyone on either side to have any issues with his job.  Other states should beg for a guy like Sam Reed to be their SoS.  He is a rePEOPLEcan.
<br />

<br />
The Demo candidate said 'recount all the votes, or recount none.' (***paraphrase - but exactly to the point), and the Repub candidate was the one with issues over recounting what has been obviously a less than accurate count so far.  Aruge for not recounting if you will, but don't expect me to listen.
<br />

<br />
Ozbee
<br />
...has worn out fingers, sorry for the bleeding eyes.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
